  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "To attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, also known as the \"Woodstock for Capitalists,\" you generally need to meet the following requirements:\n\n### 1. **Own Berkshire Hathaway Shares**\n   - **Class A or B Shares**: You must be a shareholder of record as of a specific date (typically a few weeks before the meeting). Either Class A or Class B shares qualify you for attendance.\n   - **Proof of Ownership**: You\u2019ll need your proxy materials, which include a meeting credential (usually a ticket or barcode) that verifies your shareholder status.\n\n### 2. **Request Admission Credentials**\n   - **Proxy Materials**: If you are a registered shareholder (own shares directly in your name), Berkshire Hathaway will automatically send you proxy materials, including a meeting credential, by mail.\n   - **Beneficial Owners**: If you hold shares through a broker or bank (in \"street name\"), you\u2019ll need to contact your broker or bank to request a proof of ownership letter or meeting credential.\n\n### 3. **Register for the Meeting**\n   - Berkshire Hathaway typically requires you to register in advance for the meeting. This can often be done online or by submitting the necessary credentials by mail.\n\n### 4. **Bring a Valid ID**\n   - All attendees are required to present a valid government-issued photo ID (e.g., driver\u2019s license, passport) to gain entry to the meeting.\n\n### 5. **Optional Guest Admission**\n   - Shareholders can often bring one guest to the meeting. The guest may also need to present a valid ID.\n\n### 6. **Attend Virtually (If Available)**\n   - In recent years, Berkshire Hathaway has offered a live webcast of the meeting for shareholders who cannot attend in person. You do not need to be a shareholder to access the webcast, but it is primarily intended for shareholders.\n\n### Additional Notes:\n- **Location**: The meeting is typically held at the CHI Health Center in Omaha, Nebraska.\n- **Exclusive Shopping**: Shareholders attending in person get access to an exclusive shopping event where they can purchase products from Berkshire Hathaway-owned companies.\n- **Limited Seating**: While the venue is large, seating is on a first-come, first-served basis. Arriving early is recommended.\n\nFor specific details and updates, always check the official Berkshire Hathaway website or the proxy materials sent to shareholders.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
